					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Let me translate this constraint into NES-speak:<br /><br />On this platform, DMA to OAM takes place automatically at the beginning of vertical blanking, as if $4014 writes were queued until NMI. Someone wants to run all game logic in the part of the screen occupied by the status bar, perhaps because he's doing a full-screen raster effect. This is feasible because the TG16's 65C02 CPU is clocked four times as fast as the NES's 6502.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

